---
layout: landing.njk
title: OPE
---

<!-- Hero -->
<section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-zinc-900 py-20 sm:py-28">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-30" aria-hidden="true" style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 50% at 50% -10%, #36b49f, transparent), radial-gradient(ellipse 40% 40% at 80% 100%, #DBFF75, transparent)"></div>
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 relative">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <span class="rounded-full bg-emerald-400/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-emerald-400 ring-1 ring-inset ring-emerald-400/20">Draft Specification v0.1</span>
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">Portable subscriptions for the open web</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed max-w-lg">OPE is a portable entitlement layer that lets users access gated content across any app, any feed format, any browser, and any platform. Subscribe once, read anywhere — articles in your feed reader, podcasts in your player, video in your app, or content on the web. No lock-in. No walled gardens.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="{{ '/ope/spec/' | url }}" class="rounded-full bg-emerald-500 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-emerald-400 no-underline transition-colors">Read the Spec</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/shellen/open-portable-entitlement" class="rounded-full px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-400 ring-1 ring-inset ring-zinc-400/20 hover:text-white hover:ring-zinc-400/40 no-underline transition-colors">View on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Principles -->
<section class="border-b border-zinc-900/5 py-16">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-10">
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-emerald-400/10 text-emerald-500 mb-4">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 18.3s6.7-3.3 6.7-8.3V4.2L10 1.7 3.3 4.2V10c0 5 6.7 8.3 6.7 8.3z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Entitlement, not payments</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">OPE proves you're allowed in. Payment processors handle money. Clean separation.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-emerald-400/10 text-emerald-500 mb-4">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="2" y="6" width="16" height="12" rx="2"/><path d="M13 18V4a2 2 0 0 0-2-2H9a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v14"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Truly portable</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Your subscription works in any OPE-compatible app — feed reader, podcast player, or browser. No platform lock-in.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-emerald-400/10 text-emerald-500 mb-4">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3.3 9.2a7.5 7.5 0 0 1 7.5 7.5"/><path d="M3.3 3.3a13.3 13.3 0 0 1 13.3 13.3"/><circle cx="4.2" cy="15.8" r=".8"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Works with any feed</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">RSS, Atom, JSON Feed, AT Protocol. OPE extends what you already use.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-emerald-400/10 text-emerald-500 mb-4">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M14.2 17.5v-1.7a3.3 3.3 0 0 0-3.3-3.3H4.2a3.3 3.3 0 0 0-3.3 3.3v1.7"/><circle cx="7.5" cy="5.8" r="3.3"/><path d="M19.2 17.5v-1.7a3.3 3.3 0 0 0-2.5-3.2"/><path d="M13.3 2.6a3.3 3.3 0 0 1 0 6.5"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Publisher-controlled</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Publishers issue grants and control access. Their content, their rules.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Design Philosophy -->
<section class="py-20" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">Design Philosophy</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">Four layers, cleanly separated</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mt-3">OPE occupies the space between content distribution and payment processing. Each concern stays independent.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
      <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5">
        <div class="text-xs font-medium text-zinc-400 mb-2">Layer 1</div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Content</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Articles, podcasts, video, courses, and more. Created and hosted by the publisher.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5">
        <div class="text-xs font-medium text-zinc-400 mb-2">Layer 2</div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Distribution</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Feed formats (RSS, Atom, JSON Feed, ATProto) that catalog and deliver previews.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border border-emerald-400/30 bg-emerald-400/5">
        <div class="text-xs font-medium text-emerald-500 mb-2">Layer 3 — OPE</div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Entitlement</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Verification that a user has the right to access content. Portable across apps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5">
        <div class="text-xs font-medium text-zinc-400 mb-2">Layer 4</div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Payments</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">How money changes hands. Stripe, x402, Lightning, or anything else. Out of scope.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Flow -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">The Flow</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">From feed to full content</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mt-3">Five steps from discovering content in your app to accessing the full thing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-8">
      {% for step in [{n:"1",t:"Feed",d:"Client fetches a feed and finds OPE-gated items with preview content or trailer clips."},{n:"2",t:"Discovery",d:"Client fetches /.well-known/ope to learn the publisher's capabilities."},{n:"3",t:"Authenticate",d:"Client initiates OAuth 2.0 with PKCE. User logs in with the publisher."},{n:"4",t:"Grant",d:"Publisher issues a signed grant token proving entitlement."},{n:"5",t:"Access",d:"Client presents the token and retrieves full content — article, episode, or video. Done."}] %}
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full ring-1 ring-zinc-900/10 text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-500 mb-4">{{ step.n }}</div>
        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">{{ step.t }}</h4>
        <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">{{ step.d }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- How It Works — Flipable Story Deck -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5" id="stories">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">See It In Action</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">How OPE works for real people</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mt-3">Two people, two apps, one protocol. Flip through to see how it actually works.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Story selector tabs -->
    <div class="flex gap-2 mb-8" id="story-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Story examples">
      <button class="story-tab rounded-full px-4 py-1.5 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors bg-emerald-500 text-white" data-story="alice" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="story-alice" id="tab-alice">Alice reads an article</button>
      <button class="story-tab rounded-full px-4 py-1.5 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors text-zinc-500 ring-1 ring-inset ring-zinc-900/10 hover:text-zinc-900" data-story="bob" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="story-bob" id="tab-bob">Bob listens to a podcast</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Alice's story (article) -->
    <div class="story-deck" id="story-alice" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-alice" aria-roledescription="carousel" aria-label="Alice's story walkthrough">
      <div class="relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="deck-track flex transition-transform duration-300 ease-in-out" style="transform: translateX(0)">
          {% for card in [
            {step:"1 of 6", icon:"rss", title:"Alice adds a feed", body:"Alice opens her favorite feed reader and subscribes to <strong>The Cosmic Courier</strong>, a space and science publication. Most articles show full content, but one piece — <strong>\"The Hidden Cost of Walled Gardens\"</strong> — shows only a preview. The teaser says: <em>4,500 words &middot; 18 min read.</em> Intriguing."},
            {step:"2 of 6", icon:"search", title:"Her reader discovers OPE", body:"The feed reader spots the <code>ope</code> extension in the JSON Feed and fetches the publisher's <code>/.well-known/ope</code> endpoint. One tiny JSON file tells it everything: OAuth server, content API, grant types, and pricing. No special integration required."},
            {step:"3 of 6", icon:"lock", title:"Alice taps 'Subscribe'", body:"The gated article shows a rich preview with word count, estimated read time, and a clear call-to-action. Alice taps <strong>\"Subscribe for $5/month\"</strong> and her reader opens the publisher's OAuth login. Quick and familiar."},
            {step:"4 of 6", icon:"key", title:"Authentication & grant", body:"Alice logs in with The Cosmic Courier. After a quick consent screen, the publisher issues a <strong>signed grant token</strong> — a portable JWT that proves Alice is a subscriber. Her reader stores it securely. That's it."},
            {step:"5 of 6", icon:"doc", title:"Full content, instantly", body:"Her reader presents the token to the content API and pulls down the full 4,500-word article. Alice reads it right where she is — no browser switch, no paywall interstitial, no friction. Just the article."},
            {step:"6 of 6", icon:"refresh", title:"It just keeps working", body:"Every future gated article from The Cosmic Courier is <strong>automatically accessible.</strong> The token refreshes silently in the background. Alice can also read on the publisher's website — same token, works via a browser cookie. One subscription, every surface."}
          ] %}
          <div class="deck-card flex-none w-full px-1" role="group" aria-roledescription="slide">
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5 p-6 sm:p-8 h-full">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="text-xs font-medium text-emerald-500">{{ card.step }}</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">{{ card.title }}</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">{{ card.body | safe }}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Navigation -->
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mt-6">
        <div class="flex gap-1.5 deck-dots" role="group" aria-label="Slide navigation">
          {% for i in range(0, 6) %}
          <button class="deck-dot w-2 h-2 rounded-full transition-colors {% if i == 0 %}bg-emerald-500{% else %}bg-zinc-300{% endif %}" data-index="{{ i }}" aria-label="Go to slide {{ i + 1 }}"></button>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-2">
          <button class="deck-prev w-9 h-9 rounded-full ring-1 ring-zinc-900/10 flex items-center justify-center text-zinc-400 hover:text-zinc-900 transition-colors disabled:opacity-30" disabled aria-label="Previous slide">
            <svg width="16" height="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 12L6 8l4-4"/></svg>
          </button>
          <button class="deck-next w-9 h-9 rounded-full ring-1 ring-zinc-900/10 flex items-center justify-center text-zinc-400 hover:text-zinc-900 transition-colors disabled:opacity-30" aria-label="Next slide">
            <svg width="16" height="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 12l4-4-4-4"/></svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sr-only deck-live" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bob's story (podcast) -->
    <div class="story-deck hidden" id="story-bob" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-bob" aria-roledescription="carousel" aria-label="Bob's story walkthrough">
      <div class="relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="deck-track flex transition-transform duration-300 ease-in-out" style="transform: translateX(0)">
          {% for card in [
            {step:"1 of 6", title:"Bob subscribes to a podcast feed", body:"Bob adds <strong>\"Sound and Signal\"</strong> — a music and culture podcast — to his podcast player via its RSS feed. Most episodes play fine. But Episode 12, <em>\"Why Vinyl Sounds Better (And Why It Doesn't),\"</em> only has a 2-minute teaser. The feed says: <em>57 min &middot; Season 2, Episode 12.</em>"},
            {step:"2 of 6", title:"Preview clip plays, full episode is gated", body:"Bob listens to the teaser from the RSS <code>&lt;enclosure&gt;</code>. His player detects OPE metadata on the episode and shows: <strong>\"Subscribe for $3/month for ad-free and bonus episodes.\"</strong> The full episode is behind entitlement. Fair enough — he's hooked."},
            {step:"3 of 6", title:"Bob taps Subscribe", body:"His podcast player opens the publisher's OAuth login. Bob signs up and subscribes. It's the same OAuth + PKCE flow every OPE client uses — the player doesn't need any special deal with this particular show."},
            {step:"4 of 6", title:"Grant token issued", body:"Sound and Signal verifies Bob's subscription and issues a <strong>portable grant token.</strong> It includes an <code>access</code> grant that covers all premium episodes — not just this one. His player stores it alongside tokens from other publishers."},
            {step:"5 of 6", title:"Full episode downloads", body:"The player calls the content API with the grant token. Back comes a <strong>signed media URL</strong> for the full ad-free MP3 (54.8 MB, 57 min). Bob downloads it for his commute. Show notes arrive as HTML. Nice."},
            {step:"6 of 6", title:"Every premium episode, any app", body:"New premium episodes are <strong>automatically unlocked.</strong> Signed URLs expire with the token, so links can't be shared. And here's the kicker: because the grant token is portable, Bob could switch to any other OPE-compatible podcast player without re-subscribing. His entitlement follows him."}
          ] %}
          <div class="deck-card flex-none w-full px-1" role="group" aria-roledescription="slide">
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5 p-6 sm:p-8 h-full">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="text-xs font-medium text-emerald-500">{{ card.step }}</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">{{ card.title }}</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">{{ card.body | safe }}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Navigation -->
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mt-6">
        <div class="flex gap-1.5 deck-dots" role="group" aria-label="Slide navigation">
          {% for i in range(0, 6) %}
          <button class="deck-dot w-2 h-2 rounded-full transition-colors {% if i == 0 %}bg-emerald-500{% else %}bg-zinc-300{% endif %}" data-index="{{ i }}" aria-label="Go to slide {{ i + 1 }}"></button>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-2">
          <button class="deck-prev w-9 h-9 rounded-full ring-1 ring-zinc-900/10 flex items-center justify-center text-zinc-400 hover:text-zinc-900 transition-colors disabled:opacity-30" disabled aria-label="Previous slide">
            <svg width="16" height="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 12L6 8l4-4"/></svg>
          </button>
          <button class="deck-next w-9 h-9 rounded-full ring-1 ring-zinc-900/10 flex items-center justify-center text-zinc-400 hover:text-zinc-900 transition-colors disabled:opacity-30" aria-label="Next slide">
            <svg width="16" height="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 12l4-4-4-4"/></svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sr-only deck-live" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Code Example -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-16 items-start">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 mb-4">Simple discovery, powerful access</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Publishers expose a single well-known endpoint. Reader apps handle the rest — OAuth, token management, content retrieval — all standardized.</p>
        <dl class="space-y-3">
          {% for item in [{k:"Discovery",v:"JSON manifest at a well-known URL"},{k:"Auth",v:"OAuth 2.0 with PKCE, consent, dynamic registration"},{k:"Tokens",v:"JWT, PASETO, or Macaroons — API or cookie transport"},{k:"Content",v:"Single item or batch retrieval, HTTP 402 signaling"},{k:"Web",v:"Cookie-based grants, browser unlock, cross-publisher SSO"},{k:"Feeds",v:"Non-breaking extensions with unlock URLs"}] %}
          <div class="flex gap-3 text-sm">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 whitespace-nowrap">{{ item.k }}</dt>
            <dd class="text-zinc-600">{{ item.v }}</dd>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 lg:mt-0 bg-zinc-900 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-xs">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-3 border-b border-white/5">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-white/10"></span>
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-white/10"></span>
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-white/10"></span>
          <span class="ml-2 text-zinc-500 text-xs font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)]">/.well-known/ope</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="p-5 overflow-x-auto m-0 text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">{
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"version"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"0.1"</span>,
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"oauth_server"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"https://example.com/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server"</span>,
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"entitlement"</span>: {
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"grant_url"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"https://example.com/api/entitlement/grant"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"token_format"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"jwt"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"token_mode"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"portable"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"default_ttl_seconds"</span>: <span class="text-sky-300">3600</span>
  },
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"content"</span>: {
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"endpoint_template"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"https://example.com/api/content/{id}"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"batch_endpoint"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"https://example.com/api/content/batch"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"formats_available"</span>: [<span class="text-amber-300">"html"</span>, <span class="text-amber-300">"markdown"</span>]
  },
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"grants_supported"</span>: [<span class="text-amber-300">"access"</span>, <span class="text-amber-300">"limit"</span>, <span class="text-amber-300">"signal"</span>]
}</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Audience -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5" id="for-whom">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">Who It's For</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">Built for the entire ecosystem</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {% for card in [{t:"Publishers",d:"Keep full control of your content and subscriptions while making them work everywhere.",items:["Add OPE metadata to your existing feeds","Works for articles, podcasts, video, courses, and more","Expose a single discovery endpoint","Use the reference gateway or build your own","Support any payment processor you want","WordPress, Ghost, Substack, podcast host migration paths"]},{t:"Apps & Browsers",d:"Give your users seamless access to gated content from any OPE-enabled publisher — in feed readers, podcast players, video apps, or on the web.",items:["Detect OPE extensions in any feed format","Manage per-publisher OAuth sessions","Show rich previews: word count, duration, artwork","Retrieve full articles, media files, or streaming URLs","Batch retrieval for fast offline sync","Browser unlock via cookies and HTTP 402"]},{t:"Brokers",d:"Create subscription bundles across multiple publishers. Like cable bundles, but for the open web.",items:["Aggregate entitlements across publishers","Issue broker grant tokens with Macaroons","Capability attenuation for scoped access","Single sign-on for multi-publisher access","Enable new business models"]}] %}
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-2">{{ card.t }}</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mb-4">{{ card.d }}</p>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 list-none p-0">
          {% for item in card.items %}
          <li class="text-sm text-zinc-500 flex gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 mt-1.5 shrink-0">·</span> {{ item }}</li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Grant Primitives -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5" id="grants">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">Flexible Access</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">Three simple grants, powerful access</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mt-3">OPE doesn't prescribe how entitlements are earned — it standardizes how they're proven. Every grant in the protocol is one of three primitives, each with a small set of composable fields. Fourteen common patterns (subscription, gift, trial, etc.) are named aliases — but the protocol itself only validates three types.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-5 mb-14">
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 bg-emerald-400/5 border border-emerald-400/20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
          <span class="rounded-full bg-emerald-500 w-2 h-2"></span>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-emerald-700">access</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">The reader may view this content. Access grants cover subscriptions, per-item purchases, gifts, trials, rentals, bundles, and broker access — anything where the core question is "can this person see this?"</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)]">scope · duration · transferable · source</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 bg-amber-400/5 border border-amber-400/20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
          <span class="rounded-full bg-amber-500 w-2 h-2"></span>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-amber-700">limit</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">The reader may view up to a threshold. Limit grants handle metered paywalls and locale-gated access — situations where entitlement is conditional on a quota or region rather than a binary yes/no.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)]">kind · quota · period · source</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 bg-rose-400/5 border border-rose-400/20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
          <span class="rounded-full bg-rose-500 w-2 h-2"></span>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-rose-700">signal</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">The reader has a status that unlocks treatment. Signal grants communicate things like ad-free eligibility, institutional affiliation, patron status, or family-plan membership — the content is accessible, but the experience changes.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)]">kind · source</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">Grant Builder</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600">Pick a preset to see how named grant types decompose into primitives, or build a custom grant and copy the JSON.</p>
    </div>
    <div id="grant-builder" aria-label="Grant builder widget" role="region"></div>
  </div>
</section>
